# ARP Spoofing Detection Lab

## Overview

This project demonstrates how ARP spoofing attacks can be detected through packet analysis. Using Scapy, I generated a synthetic packet capture containing normal network activity and a simulated ARP cache poisoning attack. A Python analysis tool then established baseline IP-to-MAC mappings and identified conflicting claims for the default gateway IP address.

## Files

* generate_traffic.py — Creates a synthetic network packet capture
* analyze_traffic.py — Detects conflicting ARP mappings
* lab_traffic.pcap — Packet capture for analysis

## Skills Demonstrated

* Python
* Scapy
* Packet Analysis
* Network Security
* ARP Spoofing Detection
* Wireshark
* Incident Investigation

## Example Finding

10.0.0.1 -> ['aa:bb:cc:00:00:01', 'de:ad:be:ef:00:13']

This indicates two MAC addresses claiming ownership of the same gateway IP address, a common indicator of ARP spoofing or man-in-the-middle activity.

